Gradient Investments LLC Buys New Stake in Nevro Corp. (NVRO)

					Posted by Mandy Boone on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 



Gradient Investments LLC bought a new stake in  Nevro Corp. (NYSE:NVRO) during the second quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The firm bought 4,227 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock, valued at approximately $315,000. 
Other large investors have also recently bought and sold shares of the company. State Board of Administration of Florida Retirement System increased its position in  Nevro Corp. by 1.3% in the fourth quarter. State Board of Administration of Florida Retirement System now owns 10,842 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock worth $788,000 after buying an additional 140 shares during the period.  State Street Corp increased its position in  Nevro Corp. by 5.5% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 439,751 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock worth $31,955,000 after buying an additional 22,852 shares during the period.  AQR Capital Management LLC increased its position in  Nevro Corp. by 1.8% in the fourth quarter. AQR Capital Management LLC now owns 16,635 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock worth $1,209,000 after buying an additional 295 shares during the period.  Norges Bank acquired a new position in  Nevro Corp. during the fourth quarter worth $750,000.  Finally, Teachers Advisors LLC increased its position in  Nevro Corp. by 11.3% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 42,735 shares of the medical equipment provider’s stock worth $3,105,000 after buying an additional 4,333 shares during the period. 


 Get Nevro Corp. alerts:



Shares of Nevro Corp. (NYSE:NVRO) traded down 0.61% during mid-day trading on Friday, reaching $86.33. 307,382 shares of the company’s stock were exchanged. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $76.63 and its 200 day moving average price is $85.14. Nevro Corp. has a 52-week low of $65.82 and a 52-week high of $106.93. The company’s market cap is $2.53 billion. 




Nevro Corp. (NYSE:NVRO) last posted its earnings results on Monday, May 8th. The medical equipment provider reported ($0.50) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of ($0.26) by $0.24. Nevro Corp. had a negative return on equity of 14.50% and a negative net margin of 14.49%. The firm had revenue of $68.40 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $68.71 million. During the same quarter in the previous year, the company earned ($0.33) EPS. The business’s revenue was up 64.0% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, equities research analysts predict that  Nevro Corp. will post ($1.02) EPS for the current year. 
